        <p><a href="ch73s40.html#MonstersAnimals147">Constrictor snakes</a> hunt by grabbing prey with their mouths and then squeezing it with their powerful bodies.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2313257"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals149"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Constrict (Ex):</strong></span> On a successful grapple check, a <a href="ch73s40.html#MonstersAnimals147">constrictor snake</a> deals 1d3+4 points of damage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2313296"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals150"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Improved Grab (Ex):</strong></span> To use this ability, a <a href="ch73s40.html#MonstersAnimals147">constrictor snake</a> must hit with its bite attack. It can then attempt to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity. If it wins the grapple check, it establishes a hold and can constrict.</p>
